    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen creating a scratch buffer with a filetype, LSPs don't attach to it (even with `workspace_required = false`).\n\nI use this function to make scratch buffer of a specific language and wondered why i didn't have a lsp:\n```lua\nlocal function scratch()\n\tlocal fts = vim.fn.getcompletion(\"\", \"filetype\")\n\tvim.ui.select(fts, {\n\t\tprompt = \"Scratch ft\",\n\t}, function(ft)\n\t\tif ft == nil then\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tend\n\t\tlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"filetype\", ft, { buf = buf })\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_set_current_buf(buf)\n\tend)\nend\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- install & enable jsonls (or any other lsp with workspace_required = false)\n- \n```lua\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\nvim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"filetype\", ft, { buf = buf })\nvim.api.nvim_set_current_buf(buf)\n```\n- notice how jsonls is NOT started.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLsp should start when on a scratch buffer.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-nightly+c4ac36b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, not the same lsp tsuff\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux fuhen 6.12.47 #1-NixOS SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Thu Sep 11 15:21:47 UTC 2025 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.44.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix nightly flake",
