            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Doing `vim.lsp.start` with the full config indeed start and attached the lsp to my scratch buffer.\n\n~~Doing `:LspStart jsonls` does nothing.~~ ok i looked at the source code, it just runs `vim.lsp.enable.\n\nAfter doing, `set buftype=`, running `:LspStart jsonls` does work.\n\nHere's a minimal init.lua file:\n```lua\nlocal function scratch()\n\tlocal ft = \"json\"\n\tlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n\tvim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"filetype\", ft, { buf = buf })\n\tvim.api.nvim_set_current_buf(buf)\nend\n\nvim.g.mapleader = ' '\nvim.g.maplocalleader = ' '\nvim.keymap.set(\"n\", \"<leader>s\", scratch, { desc = \"Scratch\" })\n\nvim.lsp.config('jsonls', {\n\tname = \"jsonls\",\n\tcmd = { 'vscode-json-language-server', '--stdio' },\n\tfiletypes = { 'json', 'jsonc' },\n\tinit_options = {\n\t\tprovideFormatter = true,\n\t},\n\troot_markers = { '.git' },\n})\nvim.lsp.enable({ \"jsonls\" })\n```\n\n(i create my scratch buffer with a `<leader>s`)\n\n\nIf i understood correctly, there's currently no way to have lsp autostart on a buffer with `butype=nofile`?",
